ly openspan meshlabs and chordiant the companys core product is the pega  software platform contents  history  early history  acquisitions  recent history  educational programs and conferences  products and services  clients and notable projects  see also  references  external links historyedit early historyedit alan trefler founded pegasystems in  at the age of  in cambridge massachusetts prior to founding the company in the early s trefler had developed computer systems that could play chess during the companys early years it focused on providing case management namely for companies such as american express trefler recollects that when he started pegasystems he wanted to create software that eased the heavy lifting that business people deal with as well as software that understood how businesspeople wanted things to work commenting it turns out to be a fairly hard problem to solve an article in computerworld traces business rules engine to the early s and to products from the likes of pegasystems fair isaac corp and ilog as a private company pegasystems was bootstrapped initially but did not take on outside investors the company went public in  with initial and secondary public offerings and began trading on nasdaq under the symbol pega raising several millions in funding in the process going public freed the company from needing to pursue venture capital investments pegasystems entered a period of financial trouble in the late s following a dispute with its accountants ernst  young after restating their earnings pegasystems faced an investigation by the sec which was dropped in  acquisitionsedit in march  pegasystems acquired the enterprise software company chordiant for around  million although it had clients such as citibank capital one metlife cigna wellpoint tmobile and vodafone and was described as an innovator in applying predictive analytics to customer interactions chordiant had struggled in the  recession the acquisition gave pegasystems access to new markets such as telecommunications and healthcare with pegasystems integrating chordiant and its customer relationship management crm technology into its existing operations pega cloud was introduced using amazon web services in  and in october  pegasystems acquired the mobile application developer antenna software for  million located in new jersey antenna also had bases in kraków and bangalore in october  pegasystems was described as a provider of business process management bpm and crm solutions and had its global development center in hyderabad revenues for the company grew strongly when compared to the rest of the business process management market from  until  with license revenues rising  in  the company reported that profit increases in  were fueled by demand for an upgrade to its main software product pega platform which was designed so companies could integrate data and software systems after it released its recent financial results in november  pegasystems stock rose  resulting in an  percent value increase over the prior year and a record high for the company recent historyedit pegasystems hired a cloud technology proponent to develop its cloud technology strategy in  over the following year pegasystems invested in network operations in north america and india to support its cloud services in may  pegasystems acquired the bangalorebased meshlabs a text mining and analytics software startup the times of india reported that pegasystems would integrate meshlabss text analytics software to gather unstructured social media data and decode it into actionable business insights for its clients the financial details of the transaction were not disclosed pegasystems acquired fireflydisambiguation needed in june  a cobrowsing tool funded by first round capital the startup from philadelphia pennsylvania was the companys first move into the cobrowsing market by the summer of  pegasystems remained headquartered in cambridge massachusetts with  employees by july  the company was worth around us billion by early  pegasystems remained a publicly traded company on the nasdaq with  employees  offices and more than half a billion dollars in revenue as of february  the company had active partnerships with it outsourcing companies such as tata consultancy services infosysbse wiprobse hcl technologies accenture and cognizant by september of that year companies who had built teams of pegasystems specialists included accenture ernst  young and cognizant between  and  pegasystems had average sales growth of  per year there was a steady rise in the companys share price in  with higher than expected revenues from the year prior in january  it was reported that pegasystems planned on raising its number of employees significantly and the company announced the acquisition of openspan inc in april  based in atlanta georgia openspan specialized in robotic process automation and workforce analytics software educational programs and conferencesedit pega academy was founded to provide online resources classroom training and certification for systems integrators to help them train up new pega specialists in  pegasystems announced the launch of the pega university academic program uap offering training and certification on the pega  platform for educators and students in november  pegasystems inc signed an agreement with talentsprint to train  pegacertified professionals at indian engineering colleges at the time there were  professionals trained in pegasystems technology with  percent in india the first pegaworld conference was held in  pegaworld  the companys annual users conference brought in  attendees products and servicesedit pegasystems develops and supports software for customer engagement and operations in particular as of  pega specialized in software for business process management bpm and customer relationship management crm and was seen as offering more bespoke technology than competitors such as oracle corporation or sap erp as of late  pega’s core software pegarules process commander prpc was related to bpm the companys current core software offering is its pega  platform which is accessible via cloud technologies pega  platform is the companys core offering in the market that mixes business process management crm data analytics big data social and mobile the company continuously modifies and updates the platform investing as well in cobrowsing and cloud and social media to integrate in august  the company made a strategic decision to make its software easier to use hiring teams with backgrounds in user experience by september  the company had introduced pega express pega express was designed to allow business specialists to quickly build simple applications fortune wrote in august  that pegasystems crm suite correlates data from existing marketing sales and support systems whenever a call arrives an agent is presented with an omnichannel view of the history so he or she receives a headsup into what the call might be about that in itself isnt so new but the software also uses predictive analytics to suggest solutions proactively in sprint’s case agents are presented with several different scenarios of how to handle a call in  pegasystems crm suite was listed as one of the top five largest in the crm market by david roe of cmswire alongside salesforcecom sap crm oracle crm and microsoft dynamics crm gartner mentioned pega in april  and forrester research named pegasystems a leader in customer service for enterprise clients in december  pegasystems inc in march  announced pega client lifecycle management clm an application that streamlines and automates corporate client onboarding for banks by orchestrating complex clm processes on a global scale in a single application reducing onboarding time by  percent and reducing costs by  percent in september  pegasystems released enhancements to its client lifecycle management clm and know your customer kyc applications by that time pegasystems had applied predictive analytics artificial intelligence and machine learning to its crm applications for years and among other products it is used in pegasystems decision management software clients and notable projectsedit pegasystems specializes in the following industries financial services insurance life sciences healthcare government manufacturing high tech communications and media energy and utilities while core areas have traditionally included banking and financial sectors more recent areas include manufacturing life sciences and healthcare as of  other clients included largely fortune  companies such as ing lloyds banking group baa and the state of maine which commissioned pegasystems to create a bpm system to cut administrative costs by july  paypal cisco systems and phillips were using pegasystems’ crm software and bny mellon announced they would be integrating pega into its operations as part of their efficiency strategy in  pegasystems disclosed that its clients included six of the top  global communications companies eight of the top  creditcard companies and eight of the top  global banks among them were american express hsbc united health group jpmorgan chase general motors barclays pfizer general electric and cisco systems in  american international group debuted a customer complaints application from pegasystems and also that year sprint used pegasystems to focus and rework its customer relations strategy between  and  me bank worked with pegasystems on a rebuild of its technology systems utilizing process automation according to the bank the time to open a new deposit account decreased from five days to five minutes on june   it was reported that the royal bank of scotland rbs had chosen to implement customer decisioning software developed by pegasystems in  philips and pegasystems worked together to create a new wireless patient remote monitoring system and by july philips had supplied devices to  patients pegasystems began work on a crm platform for the state 