s healthcare manufacturing insurance government high tech communications and media energy and utilities the company announced in  that it would be publicly traded on the nasdaq stock exchange pega since  the company has acquired a number of companies including antenna software firefly openspan meshlabs and chordiant the companys core product is the pega  software platform contents  history  early history  acquisitions  recent history  educational programs and conferences  products and services  clients and notable projects  see also  references  external links historyedit early historyedit alan trefler founded pegasystems in  at the age of  in cambridge massachusetts prior to founding the company in the early s trefler had developed computer systems that could play chess during the companys early years it focused on providing case management namely for companies such as american express trefler recollects that when he started pegasystems he wanted to create software that eased the heavy lifting that business people deal with as well as software that understood how businesspeople wanted things to work commenting it turns out to be a fairly hard problem to solve an article in computerworld traces business rules engine to the early s and to products from the likes of pegasystems fair isaac corp and ilog as a private company pegasystems was bootstrapped initially but did not take on outside investors the company went public in  with initial and secondary public offerings and began trading on nasdaq under the symbol pega raising several millions in funding in the process going public freed the company from needing to pursue venture capital investments pegasystems entered a period of financial trouble in the late s following a dispute with its accountants ernst  young after restating their earnings pegasystems faced an investigation by the sec which was dropped in  acquisitionsedit in march  pegasystems acquired the enterprise software company chordiant for around  million although it had clients such as citibank capital one metlife cigna wellpoint tmobile and vodafone and was described as an innovator in applying predictive analytics to customer interactions chordiant had struggled in the  recession the acquisition gave pegasystems access to new markets such as telecommunications and healthcare with pegasystems integrating chordiant and its customer relationship management crm technology into its existing operations pega cloud was introduced using amazon web services in  and in october  pegasystems acquired the mobile application developer antenna software for  million located in new jersey antenna also had bases in kraków and bangalore in october  pegasystems was described as a provider of business process management bpm and crm solutions and had its global development center in hyderabad revenues for the company grew strongly when compared to the rest of the business process management market from  until  with license revenues rising  in  the company reported that profit increases in  were fueled by demand for an upgrade to its main software product pega platform which was designed so companies could integrate data and software systems after it released its recent financial results in november  pegasystems stock rose  resulting in an  percent value increase over the prior year and a record high for the company recent historyedit pegasystems hired a cloud technology proponent to develop its cloud technology strategy in  over the following year pegasystems invested in network operations in north america and india to support its cloud services in may  pegasystems acquired the bangalorebased meshlabs a text mining and analytics software startup the times of india reported that pegasystems would integrate meshlabss text analytics software to gather unstructured social media data and decode it into actionable business insights for its clients the financial details of the transaction were not disclosed pegasystems acquired fireflydisamb